2. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the TSP on graphic metrics, which is a problem that is closely related to computational geometry. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses mathematical techniques such as matchings and integrality gaps to analyze the TSP problem. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a novel approach based on matchings, which could potentially be applied to machine learning problems. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the integrality gap of the Held-Karp relaxation, which is a measure of the computational complexity of the TSP problem.
